text: Malubiting is a mountain in the Karakoram range, in Pakistan. Malubiting is part of the Rakaposhi-Haramosh subrange. It is the 56th highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top were Horst Schindlbacher and his expedition, in 1971. == References == Category:Mountains of Gilgit-Baltistan Category:Karakoram
